{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation on another cell line yielded a significantly lower accuracy of 46%, emphasizing the substantial challenges in generalizing predictions across diverse cell lines.",
    "CMs exhibit a strong structure-function relationship, causing morphological differences to have significant impact on cardiac function.",
    "Healthy, adult CMs exhibit elongated, rod-shaped, and anisotropic morphologies with high aspects ratios (7:1 to 9.5:1) (Gerdes et al., 1992).",
    "hiPSC-CMs instead exhibit round, polygonal morphologies with significantly smaller aspect ratios, trending more to isotropic orientations (Feric and Radisic, 2016).",
    "Morphological assessment has historically required extensive time and resources to execute and is prone to user bias."
  ]
}